items.name: OshiNoKo-characters-LoHa/LoCon/FullCkpt Êé®„Åó„ÅÆÂ≠ê || Hoshino Ai / Hoshino Aquamarine / Hoshino Ruby / Arima Kana / Saito Miyako / Kurokawa Akane / Kotobuki Minami / Shiranui Frill / Sumi Yuki / ...
items.description:
UPDATE: Following the common practice, the most recent version is trained on NAI with clip skip 2

The advantage of my models is clearly the ability to put multiple characters in a same image

(I was considering training a full model with the same dataset as well, but the LoHa seems to be reasonably good at this point

The other models are otherwise trained on ACertainty
Please check the version notes for further details including the clip skip to use

Normally you should be able to use the lycoris models on a lot of different checkpoints. In case of incompatibility, you can lower lycoris weight or better, merge your base model with AC/nai.

More checkpoints can be found on the associated hugging face repository https://huggingface.co/alea31415/oshinoko

Screenshots and fan arts are respectively tagged with aniscreen and fanart. Using aniscreen gives both stronger anime style and better resemblance. Using aniscreen on style models may cause weird effects.

You may want to use ; to separate characters (see the prompts of the example images)

Characters

EP01

  • HoshinoAi (add hair ornament if you want)

  • AmemiyaGoro

  • TendojiSarina

  • Aquamarine baby

  • Aquamarine child

  • Aquamarine

  • Ruby baby

  • Ruby child

  • Ruby (add red ribbon if you want)

  • ArimaKana child

  • ArimaKana (I suppose you should add some hat)

  • SaitoIchigo

  • Miyako

  • GotandaTaishi

  • KurokawaAkane

Main improvement of EP02

  • Aquamarine

  • Ruby

Added in EP04

  • NarushimaMelt

  • KaburagiMasaya

  • KichijoujiYoriko

  • ShiranuiFrill

  • KotobukiMinami

Added at the end of the season

  • MemCho

  • KumanoNobuyuki

  • SumiYuki

  • MorimotoKengo

  • Pieyon

Comments on the most recent model:

Pieyon is not learned very well as can be seen from the example images, showing this is a more difficult task than learning the appearance of the characters

The star-shaped eyes are learned pretty well in the newest model, probably too well that it sometimes wants to put it on other characters, especially when we do inpainting

You may want to avoid this by putting related keywords in negative

I suppose this suggests a sort of character blending

Someone reported to me the EP04 version has more important character blending compared to the EP02 version

I am not sure how it would be the case for this new one as I do not have an objective way to judge this

Hopefully it works fine for you

Dataset composition

fanart 2432

screenshots

  • EP 01 1268

  • EP 02 357

  • EP 03,04 777

  • EP 05-11 2582

regularization ~35K

--

I don't need support or credit, but I would be glad to know that you are using the models I trained and find it useful.

Moreover, I would like to advocate for more franchise models.

You can take a look at my workflow https://github.com/cyber-meow/anime_screenshot_pipeline if you are interested.
You may also check this nice page https://civitai.com/articles/262/directory-of-girlpacks-character-packs for a collection of such models,

modelVersions.name: LoHa EP02
modelVersions.description:
Trained on clip skip 2.

Compared to previous versions it should be better at Aqua and Ruby while it can still do the all the other characters (though I do not bother to generate new example images for them).

This version seems to be highly unstable if you put aniscreen or fanart on any model other than ACertainty.

It also struggles to put the eyes of Aqua and Ruby in the right place, especially if you switch to other base model. If you want to inpaint their eyes correctly, the best is probably to switch to ACertainty and add aniscreen in the prompt.

It may be helpful to add red ribbon and side ponytail for Ruby, and put something like too long ponytail in negative to get the right length.

modelVersions.name: LoHa EP01
modelVersions.description:
Trained on clip skip 1.

Up to this point, Aqua, Ruby, Kana, and Akane are only trained with limited fan arts, so the quality of these characters will be largely improved later after more episodes come out.

The trained LoHa provides a smaller alternative. However, the general rule seems to indicate that the smaller the network is the easier you get style conflict. Therefore, you may want to avoid using aniscreen on any model except for ACertainty. Fanart should be fine.

After some test the model seems to work well but I don't plan to make new example images, so I only updated the last four images for some comparisons. As for the full checkpoint it seems to get the anime outfit right more frequently.

Please also adjust weight and prompt accordingly for overfitted characters. Details such as star pupils would be the first thing you lose when you switch base model. It turns out you can still get it right with aniscreen on ACertainty.

Other checkpoints can be found at https://huggingface.co/alea31415/oshinoko/tree/main/checkpoints_0414ep01/loha

modelVersions.name: LoCon EP01
modelVersions.description:
Trained on clip skip 1.

Up to this point, Aqua, Ruby, Kana, and Akane are only trained with limited fan arts, so the quality of these characters will be largely improved later after more episodes come out.

It works mostly fine, but you may need to lower weight for certain characters or base models.

It however has some difficulty putting the star in the correct eye for Aqua and Ruby. For that you have much higher success rate with the full checkpoint. For comparison please see the last four images in the examples.

It is extracted from FullCkpt EP01.

You may want to add red ribbon for Ruby.

modelVersions.name: FullCkpt Ep01
modelVersions.description:
Trained on clip skip 1.

Up to this point, Aqua, Ruby, Kana, and Akane are only trained with limited fan arts, so the quality of these characters will be largely improved later after more episodes come out.

The model is trained for 42647 steps and there are in total 4 checkpoints here

This is the 32783 step version.

If you want to put the star in the correct eye for Aqua and Ruby you would have higher chance to success with 32783 and 42647 step checkpoints. However, the last one seems to be quite overfitted. It would be much more difficult to achieve that with earlier checkpoints and extracted LoCons. For comparison please see the last four images in the examples.

On the other hand, for some characters with few training images, TendojiSarina notably, you may want to use earlier checkpoints or LoCon with lower weight to gain more flexibility.

You may want to add red ribbon for Ruby.

items.name: Ritium Refusion
items.description:
Ritium Refusion is a universal anime model.

Features Ritium Reforge Model:

  • Good clarity without hi-res fix

  • Quality backgrounds

  • Allows you to make both dark and light images

  • Excerpted anime style, with more realistic bodies.

  • You don't need to add a bunch of useless tokens like "masterpiece, best quality, 4k, 8k" and so on.

Negative Prompt

I don't recommend overloading it, keep it more simple, the following tokens will suffice for a good result:

worst quality, low quality, poorly drawn, mutated hands and fingers, bad anatomy, wrong anatomy, ugly, mutation, bad anatomy, wrong anatomy

You can control the weights of tokens: worst quality, low quality, poorly drawn to 1 - 1.4, which will change the drawing, choose the option that you like more, for myself I chose the optimal value of 1.2 .

Other parameters

Optimal values for CFG Scale 4-8

Clip Skip 1-2 - give a good result, clip skip 2 - as a rule gives out better emotions

DPM++ 2M Karass - the best sampler for anime and art

Eular A - Also very cool, but very underrated in anime models

DPM++ 2M SDE Karass - Very good sampler, but quite long

Aurora is a Stable Diffusion model, similar to its predecessor Kenshi, with the goal of capturing my own feelings towards the anime styles I desire.The name Aurora, which means 'dawn' in Latin, represents the idea of a new beginning and a fresh start.

All these Examples don't use any styles Embeddings or Loras, all results are from the model itself.

HuggingFace for Easier to Read

‚öôÔ∏è Usage

  • Settings | Value

  • Sampler | DPM++ 2M Karras

  • Clip skip | 2

items.name: Kaley Cuoco (JG)
items.description:
Kaley Cuoco is an American actress, mainly known for her role as Penny in The Big Bang Theory series.

450-step TI trained on a dataset of 18 images with my new settings. This is a bit of an experiment, mainly based on this (ongoing) conversation, particularly on the comments and expertise shared by @7016jayAlex, for which I want to give him special thanks. Basically, what's changed is that I have reduced my dataset to 18 images and increased my gradient accumulation steps to 6, so that I now run a full epoch per step (3 batch size * 6 gradient = 18, the exact number of pics in my dataset). That way, I can achieve similar results to the ones I've been posting until now with around 400, 450 steps, as in this case. I gotta say it takes me basically the same time to train, though. I'll train a few more TIs following this new procedure and then decide whether I like it better or worse (or maybe exactly the same) as my previous one. For now, I gotta say it looks pretty good! :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

items.name: Musubi | Sekirei
items.description:
Lora trained on Musubi from Sekirei

Master model anime: Based65, meinaunreal

2,5D: fantasticmixReal_V30 (this one is also more realistic), ReV Animated

negative embeddings: embedding:bad-hands-5, embedding:ng_deepnegative_v1_75t, embedding:bad-artist, embedding:EasyNegative

Recommended settings:

  • Make sure you are aware on the usage instructions of LORA

  • VAE: orangemix.vae (for 2,5D pictures), vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned (for realistic models), kl-f8-anime2, blessed2.vae (for anime models)

  • Sampler: DPM++ SDE Karras or DPM++ 2M Karras

  • Steps: 20 to 35

  • Clipskip: 1 or 2

  • Upscaler : img2img in comfyui using 4x-UltraMix_Smooth

  • CFG Scale : 5 to 9 (mostly 7 and 8)

  • LORA weight for txt2img: 0.5-1 (for the examples i mostly used 0.7)

  • Denoise strength for img2img: 0.4 to 0.7

If you want the exact same settings, just drag and drop the picture into ComfyUI because this time I included the metadata of the pictures

Trained with based65 checkpoint

for the pictures i used comfyui

for the most accurate pictures i would recommend using this costum node for comfyui: cutoff-for-comfyui

or this for automatic1111: no-more-color-contamination

items.name: Natalia Trubnikova (70s)
items.description:
Soviet ballerina. Unearthly, ultimate beauty. She does not have many roles in the film, but one is especially beautiful.

It is thanks to this film that this model was created. Honestly, this is one of the most complex and unstable models that I have created. Alas, there are very few high-quality photographs, very few different images.

The model was created on the basis of frames from the film "June 31" 1978. This is one of the biggest problems with this model. This is the hairstyle of the actress. She is very special in this film.

I recommend using token "braid" to negative prompt. You can boost it up to 1.2-1.3. It is advisable to use token enhancements in the hairstyle style.

The model works in the range of 0.7-0.8.

items.name: animeTWO
items.description:
Introducing the "animeTWO" model, or a2 for short! It is a general purpose anime model based on my previous animeElves model. While both previous models were merges of models I collected, the animeTWO model is a pure finetune with a few tweaks and it is made to follow prompts more precisly than my previous models, (no accidental elves anymore!).

The a2 model can make anime elves, obviously, but unlike the old models its general purpose and can be applied to many, many topics! Aliens, monsters, spaceships, retro computers, slime monsters, cats and catgirls, chibi cthulhus etc.! It also can create stunning landscapes. Like the my previous models, a2 is in no case itended to be lewd, but can be forced to do so, viewer discretion is advised.

No VAE is baked in so you are free to choose yours, but I still reccomend the standard 1.5 vae.

Please consider joining my Patreon! Advanced SD, and other Generative AI tutorials, guides, and tips, from a female content creator (me!) patreon.com/theally - it's popular! Over 200 Patrons are trusting me to explain how things work!

Note: The prompt metadata on Civitai is broken due to using the Dynamic Prompt extension for WebUI. It includes my positive in the negative prompt. Careful :)

Mix IV - What!?

This is the current pinnacle of my merging "career"; a noise-offset enabled, realism-focused merge.

We started with TheAlly's Mix - SD1.4 + Waifu 1.3 + NovelAI. Hundreds of test mixes, and three release mixes later, we've arrived at the Holy Grail of TheAlly's Mix Merges (until version V).

This mix contains 75% TheAlly's Mix III, with the other 25% being a huge, crazy, block-merge mashup of realistic-focused models such as the excellent;

  • Uber Realistic Porn Merge (URPM) v1.1

  • QGO-10b

  • Realistic Vision V2.0


I tried my best to fix hands using some of the common block-merge hand-repair techniques, editing the IN00, IN01, IN02 blocks, and they've turned out not bad, have seen worse, still not great.

What's it good at?

Everything! Wild results. Awesome portraits. Check out the example prompts and try them for yourself. I will say, if you want the best from it, you're going to have to work at your prompts.

Recreating my sample images?!

Some of my sample images are created with ControlNet, to get poses and compositions from my previous generations - you'll never be able to reproduce those. Others, it's possible, but some do use Patron exclusive embeddings. The sample images are meant to show what's possible with a model. Use your imagination! I do have a tutorial on Patreon on recreating my images, the common settings I use, etc.

items.name: Catherine - Catherine: Full Body
items.description:
What does it do you ask? The bodacious blonde from Catherine: Full Body comes for you to play with on Stable Diffusion. Now would you choose her or Katherine is the question? There weren't a TON of high quality pictures of her on the internet, so I had to make due with what did exist. Overall, I think the quality still came out satisfactory.

How to use it: Simple for this Lora:

CatherineVG - Main and only trigger needed.

Extra, Extra!: Should be well trained and usable in most models. Images shown for example.

Picture Descriptions:

1-3: AnythingV3 using just this Lora with simpler prompts.

4: AnythingV3 combo'd with my in progress Hourglass Locon.

5: AnythingV3 combo'd with my in progress Dominatrix Locon.

6: AnythingV3 combo'd with my in progress Defaultz_17 style Locon.

7: AnythingV3 combo'd with my in progress Knight-ify Locon.

8: AnythingV3 combo'd with my in progress Jiangshi-ify Locon.

9: AnythingV3 combo'd with my released Symbiote Locon.

10: AbyssOrange with just this Lora.

11: PerfectWorld using just this Lora.

12: ChilloutMix using just this Lora.

How was it trained?

It was trained on animefull_final with 17 images with the usual self-pruning and tagging and a wide range of different images. I like keeping my prompts simple for the first few pictures so that you can see it without a whole bunch of mumbo jumbo. Make your pictures better than mine though!

What's next for this?

Hopefully this one is better, if not I'll update it again.

What's next that isn't this?

More character Loras. (Viper from Nikke, Spectre Tenebria from E7, Zephia from Fire Emblem Engage, Ivy from Soul Calibur 5, Heine from Combatants Will Be Dispatched, Conqueror Lilias from E7, Evelynn from LoL (both base and All Out version), Tharja from Fire Emblem, Laharl-Chan from Disgaea 5, Miku from Idaten Deities, Kuribayashi Shino from GATE, Rin Sohma from Fruits Basket, Kasumi from P5, Ann from P5, Ikumi Mito from Food Wars, Alice Nakiri from Food Wars, Chika Fujiwara from Kaguya-sama, Lulu from FF10, Momo from My Hero, Sheik from Zelda, Vivy from Vivy, Lucoa and Tohru from Dragon Maid, Dominique de Sade from Vanitas, and Dos from One Punch Man.) And maybe Wilhelm van Astrea, my favorite Re:Zero husbando or a Prinny from Disgaea.

V2's of some of the previous Loras. Specifically make them more diversely acceptable with other models and LORA's.

I also have some more quite NSFW Locon's. I decided to list them as well, so if people have preferences on which to fix up first let me know. Specifically, Demonic Transformation, being stepped on, Robotification, Defeated (decently NSFW defeat scenario for the waifu), Petrified (I'm unsure if I should bother with this one anymore), Infection (this one is VERY nsfw, as the waifu is completely infected), Dominatrix (waifu becoming a dominatrix), Brainwashing Machine, Tentacles, Pillory, Masked Evil (A mask that possess' the waifu), Latex Corruption, Combat Drone (hard to describe but basically making them a mindless sci-fi combat warrior), JAV Supervillain, Jiangshi (Transforms into a Jiangshi), Mind Flayer Defeat, Blacked, Harem Outfits, Hourglass Figure (just to make your waifu curvy), and Holding a Leash.

And, uh, I want to make a few "normal" Locon's so I have an "knight-ify" your character one coming up. And a forest fairy one as well. And a officer one. And a barbarian one.

Additionally, I love the style of Defaultz_17, so I'm making a Locon to mirror that.

Or just give me some random suggestion or priority opinions. That works too.

items.name: Standing Split Sex
items.description:
This is a LoRA to generate Standing Split Sex.

  • I suggest using this at 0.8-1.0 weight for best results but make sure to always play around with the weight.

  • It was generated and only tested using AOM2, AOM3 A1, My Own Mix, OrangeMix VAE and AnythingV3 VAE.

  • Always add this to the prompt to activate it: ekstandsplit, 1boy, penis, sex, standing, standing split, standing sex

  • It was trained on 512x512 - so, I suggest generating in 512x512 then upscaling to an higher resolution.

  • It works best on anime models or models trained on NAI. It may or may not work on realistic.

You can make small variations by adding these tags individually or together.

Note: Some of these will break generations or enhance them, depending on what tags you're putting together.

  • Motion lines - will add the effect of motion and add small variations.

  • From Side - will add like three or four new variations.

  • Standing on one leg - will help with generating and add like two new variations. (The guy is more inclined to grab her leg)

  • leg up - will help with generating and add a few variations.

Known Issues (As far as I know)

  • Sometimes the man won't be generated but his penis will generate.

  • Sometimes her leg won't fully generate or when it does - She will have a hand instead of a foot.

  • Sometimes - It will generate doggystyle or some deformed demon.

  • Sometimes an extra arm will appear from the girl.

  • She will appear to be pressing against nothing with her arms - This is because the dataset has alot of pictures of them against the wall but you can fix this by adding against wall.

Follow me on Twitter for updates- https://twitter.com/TrueHeroBang

Everything I'm making will always be free but if you want to show a little bit more support, you can buy me a coffee - https://ko-fi.com/ekune

items.name: Mitsubishi 3000GT VR-4
items.description:
https://t.me/stdif_kos

Following the successful showing of the Mitsubishi HSR and Mitsubishi HSX concept cars at the 1989 Tokyo Motor Show,[7] Mitsubishi unveiled the new GTO as a 2+2 seating grand touring car in order to compete with the Mazda Cosmo, Nissan 300ZX, Subaru SVX, and the Toyota Supra. They resurrected the GTO name, and the car went on to serve as Mitsubishi's flagship for the remainder of the decade. Despite the cachet of the badge at home, it was marketed as the Mitsubishi 3000GT and as the Dodge Stealth outside Japan; the company was concerned that connoisseurs would object to the evocative nameplate from the Ferrari 250 GTO and Pontiac GTO being used on a Japanese vehicle.

Each was built on the same production line at Mitsubishi's plant in Nagoya, Japan.[8] Its Japanese introduction coincided with the softening Japanese economy, subsequently known as the "bubble economy".

JDM GTOs were marketed at Mitsubishi's Car Plaza retail chain, with JDM buyers paying additional annual road tax as well as elevated taxes for being classified as a large car by Japan's exterior dimension regulations.

A Dodge Stealth was scheduled as a 1991 Indianapolis 500 pace car, until the United Auto Workers (UAW) rejected it because of its Japanese rather than US-manufacture. A prototype of the Dodge Viper was substituted in place of it.[9] Still used as a backup pace car, eventual race winner Rick Mears received a Dodge Stealth for winning the race and dealers sold pace car replica editions, as the Viper did not begin production until later that year.[10]

items.name: CoffeeMix
items.description:
CoffeeMix is intended primarily for producing more cartoony, flatter anime pictures that tend to have more pronounced lineart and cel shading.

This model is not intended for detailed illustrations so backgrounds will be on the simpler/cartoony side. It works best with simple, short prompts and I highly encourage trying fewer tokens(prompt length and embeddings) if you dislike the results.

Use EasyNegative on negative prompt. VAE is baked-in.

My recommended sampler is DPM++ 2M Karras with 20 sampling steps, but other samplers work just fine. Model is pretty sfw unless you add nsfw into positive prompt.

If you like the model, please consider tipping me a coffee.

modelVersions.name: v2.0
modelVersions.description: v2: Finetuned artstyle, better hands, backgrounds have more definition and output will generate much more interesting faces when subject is farther away

modelVersions.name: v1.5
modelVersions.description: v1.5: More definition in lineart, cel shading. LoRAs work better and eyes are more detailed.

items.name: MadeInAbyss CafeMix
items.description:
This is the first merge I've made, go easy on me :)

The Model combines two main checkpoints, the MIA model (Original post) and unstableinkdream7.5Anime. Because the original MIA model is here, you can prompt characters such as Riko and Nanachi just by typing "(Riko)" or "(Nanachi). The model also works great without being MIA themed, it creates a brilliant balance of character detail mixed with a balanced backdrop.

In the (Original post) download, you can find a list of prompts on the google docs that the original creator trained. The backgrounds hardly work with this merge however most of the characters still do, to some degree, with the best success being with:

  • Nanachi (sometimes fluffy sometimes not)

  • Riko

  • Prushka

  • Marulk (mostly generates female marulk, prompt "flat chest".)

  • Human Mitty

  • Jirou (kinda works)

  • Mitty (Not accurate, creates horrors, Bondrewd approved)

  • Bondrewd (sometimes works)

Nanachi should be prompted along with some sort of chest covering due to the human nature at which this model generates them. (Or don't, it's not up to me.) With this, it should go without saying that this model "Can" generate NSFW but is not its primary focus. Use "NSFW, Nipples" in negatives to help with this.

There are LoRas out there for some of the characters that will be able to make up for what this merge lacks, the merge mostly excels in balancing good character detail with good background detail and I personally really like it.


This merge also works with other LoRas (most of the time).

items.name: Arad Winwin
items.description:
A LoRA trained on a dataset of profession photos of Arad Winwin, and adult film character. Trained on danbooru tags and each image. Doesn't do close-up facial details very well most of the time, but gets the body features above the hip and his arm tattoo incredibly well.

Other recommended tags that tend to help (mix and match): solo, arm tattoo, short hair, black hair, facial hair, beard, undercut, bara, mature male, 1boy, nipples, pectorals, upper body, male focus, nude, briefs, underwear, navel, navel hair, shirtless

I recommend a homoerotic based model. I use a custom merge of homoerotic_v2 & Protogen Nova with bits of other models for generating mostly.

modelVersions.name: v2.0
modelVersions.description:
Retrained on homoerotic_v2 and with more images (some of slightly lower quality) to add diversity and stabilize the face.

This version of the model generates more consistently normal looking faces and more variety, but is slightly worse at conforming to more specific booru tags and the face is consistently more off from Arad's real life face. Skin also is more airbrushed. I may try some other techniques in the next one.

modelVersions.name: v1.0
modelVersions.description: Initial training. Not yet trained on up-close faces. Does well with torso, but you will have to be specific with tagging and use the recommended trigger words to get the best effect. Use danbooru tags.
